### Webox — .gitignore
# Goal: ignore build artifacts, transient state, secrets, and editor noise.
# Anything tracked here would either bloat the repo, leak data, or break
# reproducibility across contributors.

### Project-specific
archive/

### Build / release artifacts
/dist/
/build/
/bin/
/webox
/webox.exe
*.exe
*.test
*.out
*.prof
*.cpuprofile
*.memprofile
/coverage.out
/coverage.html
/coverage/

### GoReleaser
/dist/
/.goreleaser/cache/

### Go module cache (rarely committed)
/vendor/

### Editor / IDE
.idea/
# Allow shared project defaults; ignore user-specific files.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.history/

### OS metadata
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

### Webox runtime state — never commit (would leak project layout + maybe creds)
*.log
webox.log
webox.log.*
pending_cleanups.json
secrets.enc
secrets.enc.bak
config.json
config.lock
known_hosts

### Local env / secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
id_*
*.crt
.netrc

### Mock testing artifacts (kept locally only)
testing/fixtures/**/.captured
testing/cassettes/**.recorded

### Go workspace files (avoid leaking dev paths)
go.work
go.work.sum

### Cosign signing transient
*.cosign.bundle
*.cosign.pem
*.sig
/landing
/main-view-mock.png

### Private operations room — NEVER commit (strategy drafts, partnerships,
### portfolio notes, metrics snapshots). Lives in repo for AI agent access
### but is gitignored. See .local/README.md (if you have one) for layout.
/.local/
